"}', 'faq' => '[{"question":"What makes the TimberTouch\\u2122 different from a standard resin folding chair?","answer":"The defining difference is the wood grain finish. Most commercial resin folding chairs come in plain white or black, which works fine for utility use but can look stark at weddings, rustic outdoor events, or any setting where aesthetics matter to the client. The TimberTouch\\u2122 gives those events a warmer, more natural look without introducing the maintenance requirements of real wood."},{"question":"Can these chairs be used outdoors?","answer":"Yes. The resin construction and UV-treated finish are designed for outdoor use. The surface resists sun exposure without fading and handles moisture without warping or degrading. As with any event chair, storing them indoors between events will extend their lifespan."},{"question":"Is the wood grain finish real wood?","answer":"No. The finish is a textured resin surface designed to replicate the appearance of wood grain. It is waterproof, UV resistant, and will not crack, split, or require refinishing the way real wood does. For operations that want the aesthetic of a wood chair with the durability and low maintenance of resin, that is the practical advantage of this construction."},{"question":"How do these chairs stack and store?","answer":"The TimberTouch\\u2122 folds flat and stacks for storage and transport. At 10 lbs. per chair, they are manageable for quick event setups and teardowns. For operations moving large quantities, EventStable carries a selection of folding chair dollies designed for efficient bulk transport."}]', 'default_color' => 'Dark Walnut', 'color_variants' => '[{"label":"Dark Walnut","swatch":"images\\/products\\/timbertouch-resin-folding-chair-dark-walnut-with-ivory-pad\\/f99d22291756.png","gallery":["images\\/products\\/timbertouch-resin-folding-chair-dark-walnut-with-ivory-pad\\/06ff639f9068.jpg","images\\/products\\/timbertouch-resin-folding-chair-dark-walnut-with-ivory-pad\\